Materials and Methods   2.1 Datasets   Training and Validation Samples    This study utilizes existing data from the German National Cohort  (GNC: https://nako.de/ ),  the BiDirect study ( https://www.medizin.uni -muenster.de/en/ep i/research/projects/bidirect.html ),  the Marburg -M√ºnster -Affective -Cohort Study ( FOR2107/ MACS: https://for2107.de/ ), the Information  eXtraction from Images (IXI) ( https://brain -development.org/ixi -dataset/ ) and the Beijing Normal  University  dataset  (http://fcon_1000.projects.ni trc.org/indi/retro/BeijingEnhanced.html ).
The minimal preprocessing is done using the  implementations of HD -BET ( https://github.com/MIC -DKFZ/HD -BET) and fastai_scans  (https://github.com/renato145/fastai_scans ).

For the processed  data, the T 1-weighted images are preprocessed with the commonly used  CAT12 toolbox  (built 1450 with SPM12 version 7487 and Matlab 2019a; http://dbm.neuro.uni - jena.de/cat ) with default parameters.
The implementation of the minimal preprocessing, the  training routine and the pretrained models is ma de available at https://github.com/wwu - mmll/fastbrainage .
